  "texts": [
    "1) Initialization:As with other graph-based models, GAT starts with nodes in the graph, each associated with a feature vector.",
    "These features can represent various characteristics of the nodes.",
    "2) Self-Attention Mechanism and Attention Computation:GAT introduces an attention mechanism similar to what is used in sequence-tosequence models in natural language processing.",
    "The attention mechanism allows each node to focus on different neighbors when aggregating information.",
    "It assigns different attention coefficients to the neighboring nodes, making the process more flexible."
